HEADWORD: Crowned
<hw>Crowned</hw> <pr>(kround)</pr>, <pos>p. p. & a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Having or wearing a crown; surmounted, invested, or adorned, with a
crown, wreath, garland, etc.; honored; rewarded; completed; consummated;
perfected.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Crowned</xex> with one crest.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Shak.</au> ⟦ldquo⟧<xex>Crowned</xex> with conquest.⟦rdquo⟧
<au>Milton.</au>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>With surpassing glory <qex>crowned</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Great; excessive; supreme.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Chaucer.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crowner</ent>⟦br⟧
